ositions and count\n- The character moves to different positions\n- Maybe the goal is to reach a state where all green blocks are collected or the character reaches a target\nLet me try ACTION7 again to see more of the pattern. I should also track the character position and green block count across multiple ACTION7 calls.", "kind": "reasoning", "inContext": false}, {"label": "TOOL CALL: python", "content": "<tool_call>\n<function=python>\n<parameter=code>\n# ACTION7 cycles through states. Let me track the pattern more carefully.\n# Let me do several ACTION7 calls and track green block count + character position\n\nstates = []\nfor i in range(5):\n    seg = current_frame.segmentation\n    green_count = sum(1 for n in seg['nodes'] if n['color'] == 'N')\n    char_pos = None\n    for n in seg['nodes']:\n        if n['color'] == 'b':\n            b = n['boundary']\n            cols = [p[1] for p in b]\n            char_pos = (min(cols), max(cols))\n            break\n    states.append((green_count, char_pos))\n    print(f\"State {i}: {green_count} green blocks, char cols {char_pos}\")\n    \n    result = action(['ACTION7'])\n    if last_action_result.get('done') or last_action_result.get('level_completed'):\n        print(\"Level completed!\")\n        break\n\n# Print all states\nprint(\"\\nState sequence:\")\nfor i, (g, c) in enumerate(states):\n    print(f\"  {i}: {g} green, char {c}\")\n</parameter>\n</function>\n</tool_call>", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "TOOL RESULT: python", "content": "State 0: 7 green blocks, char cols (38, 39)\nState 1: 7 green blocks, char cols (32, 33)\nState 2: 7 green blocks, char cols (26, 27)\nState 3: 7 green blocks, char cols (20, 21)\nState 4: 7 green blocks, char cols (20, 21)\n\nState sequence:\n  0: 7 green, char (38, 39)\n  1: 7 green, char (32, 33)\n  2: 7 green, char (26, 27)\n  3: 7 green, char (20, 21)\n  4: 7 green, char (20, 21)", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}], "hasExactModelContext": false, "requestIn